@226=~This potion confers invisibility similar to the second level wizard spell of the same name, causing the imbiber to vanish from sight and be undetectable by normal vision or even infravision. Of course, the imbiber is not magically silenced, and certain other conditions can render the imbiber detectable. Even allies cannot see the invisible creature or his gear, unless these allies can normally see invisible things or employ magic to do so. Items dropped or put down by the imbiber become visible. The spell remains in effect until it is magically broken or dispelled, until the imbiber cancels it, until the imbbiber attacks any creature, until the imbiber's location is given away by manipulating objects or initiating dialog, or until 4 turns have passed. Thus the imbiber can move, open doors, talk if spoken to first, climb stairs, or drop items while remaining invisible. However, if the imbiber picks up objects, initiates dialog or attacks, the invisibility is broken, although the invisibility enables a surprise attack.

