Area of effect: 30-feet radius

Special: Agannazar's Scorcher
Damage: 6D6
Range: 90 feet
Area of effect: 1 creature

Usable by:
 Mage~
 
@292=~White crystalline motes spray forth from the wand in a cone towards the victim striking square in the chest with numbing force. The temperature inside the cone is deadly, and damage is 6d6 +6 with a save vs. wands for half.

STATISTICS:

Special: Cone of Cold
Damage: 6D6 + 6 (save vs. wands for half)
Range: 10 feet
Usable by:
 Mage~
 
@293=~The possessor of the wand can discharge a bolt of lightning. As it passes through a creature, it does 6d6 + 6 points of damage with a save vs. wand for half damage. The bolt will continue through the target and proceed to 'rebound' until expended.

STATISTICS:

Special: Lightning bolt
Damage: 6D6 + 6 (save vs. wands for half)
Range: 100 feet
Usable by:
 Mage~
 
@294=~This wand will emit a gold beam of energy at its targets up to a maximum range of 90 feet, effecting a 20-feet cube. If the target creatures fails their save vs. wands, they will fall into a deep, comatose sleep for 6 rounds.

STATISTICS:

Special: Sleep unless victim saves vs. wands
Range: 90 feet
Area: 20-feet radius
Duration: 6 rounds
Usuable by:
 Mage~
 
@295=~This wand will summon four 2nd-level monsters, which appear within the area of effect and attack the user's enemies. They remain until the spell duration expires, or the monsters are slain. These creatures vanish when slain. If no opponent exists to fight and the wizard can communicate with them, the summoned monsters can perform other services for the summoning wizard. The monsters will obey simple telepathic commands, but will not follow the caster out of the area that they were summoned in.

