@307=~Amulet of Immunity to Charm: 'Dryad-bane'
Many years ago there lived in the Snowflake Mountains in Amn an orc named Brashk. He was known for his exceptional size and strength but even more so for his hatred of the forests to the east and the dryads that lived therein. Through unknown means Brashk somehow got hold of this amulet and quickly discovered its power. He gathered hordes of orcs from nearby and launched large attacks on the dryads, their trees and all other woodland beings unfortunate enough to cross their paths. The orc army was in high spirits at the sight of a leader who would not fall victim to the magics of the dryads. However, to the doom of Brashk and his horde, the burning woods soon drew attention from elsewhere. A female ranger managed to gather several druids and even wood elves, and unite these for a short time to fight Brashk. This group was joined by other intelligent inhabitants of the woods that had not yet perished and together they put an end to the life of Brashk and nearly everyone with him. It is not known who became the new owner of the amulet and it has not been involved in actions as dramatic as those of the forest burning orc since.

