@359=~Gloves of Thievery~

@360=~Gloves of Thievery: 'Bailum's Curse'
The history of this pair of gloves is closely related to another magical item, the Ring of Damnation. The gloves were given to Bailum, a thief from Silverymoon, over 90 winters ago as a reward for an old spellbook he had recovered for a wizard in that city. During this mission Bailum had learned of the location of an old tomb in the area, and with the aid of his newfound gloves he set out to explore it. Bailum found a tomb with no guardians or treasures, except for a simple ring discovered in a hidden cache. He did not think much of it and intended to put it in his backpack but suddenly noticed that he had removed his gloves and put the ring on. The next thing he remembered was standing outside the house of the mage who had given him the gloves, pulling his sword from that mage's stomach. Bailum turned around, blood still dripping from the blade, and faced two approaching guards. As they had nearly reached him, two black bolts shot from the ring and both guards fell dead to the ground. An instant later Bailum found himself in an new location, the corpse of an old friend lying before him. In a similar fashion the presence of Bailum carved a path of destruction from the North down through the Sword Coast, following the tracks of Bailum's previous journeys. It all came to an end when Bailum reached Athkatla in Amn. The sudden death of a merchant in that city caught the attention of Cosmo, who permanently dispelled the magic of the ring and freed Bailum from its curse.

