@509=~Ring of Health~ 

@510=~Ring of Health: 'The Druid's Reward'
This ring was once in the possession of a young aspiring paladin named Soinyr, whose father had given it to him in the hope that Soinyr might gain an advantage over the other would-be knights. During one of the final tests given to him by his order, Sionyr came upon a forest that he had to travel through to reach his destination. Unfortunately, he quickly became lost and nightfall was not far off. Soon he found himself stumbling blindly through the undergrowth in the dark of the night, nearly panicing and without any knowledge of where he was heading. After having reached a blind end, he tried to go back but suddenly caught sight of a gigantic wolf only a few steps behind him. It was twice the size of any wolf he had ever seen before, and without hesitation he drew his sword and attacked it. The sword found its mark but the wound immediately enraged the beast and it let loose a mighty howl. In a matter of moments several other wolves appeared and they all slowly encircled him. Fearing his final moment to be upon him, Sionyr stood with his back against a tree and both hands on his sword, determined to kill as many of the wolves as possible before their teeth and claws would find their way through his armor. Just then, a stranger stepped into the circle of wolves from out of nowhere. The wolves calmed down with a wave of his hand and a few gentle words made them leave. The stranger then turned his attention on Soinyr who still stood with his sword in his hands, failing to believe what he had just witnessed. The man presented himself as Reol, druid of the forest, and told Soinyr to follow him, leading him all the way to the edge. Here he told Sionyr that if he intended to return to the forest he would like him to treat its inhabitants more according to their behaviour and less on prejudice. Soinyr realized the folly of his actions and felt that he had to repay the druid for his kindness. He then remembered his magical ring and, although he did not know what it did, he gave it to Reol in the hope that it might somehow aid him. Sionyr departed and Reol returned to his woods. The ring was later given to Reol's daughter who took it with her to other lands.

STATISTICS:

Constitution: set to 16~ 

