@516=~Ring of Lightning Resistance: 'Siphuyrus'
Siphuyrus, a wizard from Sigil, created this ring many years ago. He was very interested in the Quasielemental Plane of Lightning and this ring would protect him on his journeys there. Unfortunately, another wizard came to know of Siphuyrus' ring and wanted to possess it. He attempted to take it from Siphuyrus by force and in the magical battle between the two, a portal was somehow triggered and Siphuyrus fell through it. The portal took him to the world of Toril on the Prime Material Plane, to a place along the Sword Coast called the Fields of the Dead. As all his possessions were left in Sigil, Siphuyrus was unable to travel back to his home. He wandered this area for some time until he came upon a travelling alchemist who happened to have the needed component for his spell. Siphuyrus paid for it with this ring and the alchemist took it with him to Baldur's Gate where it passed onto another buyer.

