@863=~Short Sword +1, +4 vs. undead: 'Blackflame'
This sword has a long history of slaying undead. Countless skeletons, zombies, ghouls and ghasts, and even greater undead such as skeleton warriors, have fallen before its wielders. During one particular event its magic did little to even the odds against the enemy, however. In early Marpenoth 1349 DR Obran the Odd, a devout priest of Lathandar, gathered a small horde of fanatical followers he had gained over the years and assaulted Warlock's Crypt, the stronghold of Larloch the Lich. Warlock's Crypt is normally a place the people of the Sword Coast dare not come within 50 miles of, or even speak loudly of, lest they gain the attention of Larloch, but Obran's hatred of the undead knew no bounds and he saw Warlock's Crypt as the ultimate blight upon the face of Faern. It certainly holds the greatest collection of ultra-powerful undead and Obran's small army was only starting to get close to the place when darkness and death descended upon them. Blackflame was wielded by a human battlemage that day whose judgement was not nearly as clouded as that of his comrades. After the initial turmoil and confusion had settled he saw Obran coming towards him with the dead, empty stare and hungry snarl of an undead being, and knew they were facing impossible odds. He teleported away from the battlefield and counted himself lucky for being alive. He threw away the sword and abandoned adventuring from that day on.

