@987=~Cure Disease (Abjuration)

Level: 3
Sphere: Healing, Necromantic
Range: Touch
Duration: Instantaneous
Casting Time: 1 round
Area of Effect: Creature touched
Saving Throw: None

By laying her hands upon a sickly person, the caster can cure almost any disease with this spell.  The cure is permanent, but this does not grant the recipient of the spell immunity from further afflictions.  Blindness and deafness are also cured with this spell.  Some magically created diseases may not be curable by this spell.~

@988=~Zone of Sweet Air 
(Abjuration) 

Level: 3
Sphere: Elemental Air, Wards
Range: 30 yards
Duration: Instantaneous
Casting Time: 6
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: None

Zone of Sweet Air repels all noxious elements from poisonous vapors (including magically created vapors such as Cloudkill).  This spell will dismiss all clouds in the entire area that the caster is currently in.  The spell offers no protection against poisonous vapors created by a dragon's breath weapon (such as the chlorine gas of a green dragon).~

@989=~Summon Insects 
(Conjuration/Summoning)

Level: 3
Sphere: Animal
Range: 30 yards
Duration: 1 round/level
Casting Time: 1 round
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: Negates

The summon insects spell attracts a cloud or swarm of normal insects to attack one enemy of the caster.  This swarm gathers at a point chosen by the caster, within the spell's range, and attacks any single creature the caster points to.  The victim may make a saving throw vs. spell to escape the swarm.  Otherwise, the victim receives 4 points of damage per round for the duration of the spell.  In addtion, the victim fights with a -2 penalty to his attack roll and a +2 penalty to his Armor Class.~

@990=~Call Woodland Beings 
(Conjuration/Summoning)

Level: 4
Sphere: Animal
Range: 1 outdoor area
Duration: 2 rounds/level
Casting Time: 1 round
Area of Effect: Special 
Saving Throw: None

By means of this spell, the caster is able to summon 1D4 dryads.  The chance for a successful call is 60%, plus 1% per caster level.  Any dryads answering the call are favorably disposed towards the spellcaster and give whatever aid they can.  However, if any members of the caller's party are of evil alignment, the creatures are allowed a saving throw vs. spell (with a +4 bonus) to escape the call.  Naturally, this spell only works outdoors.~

