@1097=~Conjure Elemental
(Conjuration/Summoning)

Level: 5
Range: 60 yards
Duration: 5 rounds/level
Casting Time: 1 round
Area of Effect: Summons 1 elemental
Saving Throw: None

There are actually three spells in the Conjure Elemental spell. The wizard is able to conjure an air, earth, or fire elemental with this spell. Conjured elementals have 8 HD. The conjured elemental must be controlled by the wizard - the spellcaster must concentrate on the elemental doing his commands - or it turns on the wizard and attacks. If the wizard is wounded, his concentration is broken. There is always a 2% chance that the elemental turns on its conjurer regardless of conjuration. This check is made at the end of the second and each succeeding round.
Note: the spellcaster may choose to stop concentrating via the special abilities menu.~

